I am Zarbalatrax, King of Shadow Time.
Tell me, what do you fear?
Ahh, I see. The paradox of the dark. Either something is there, or it is not. Tell me, are you brave?
To be alone is to face your true self. Tell me, do you like what you see?
The Beast. I don't blame you. Tell me, do you fear possession of yourself or a loved one?
You wake up bound to a chair. The room is pitch black. Your eyes struggle to process the dark.
Give up. It's not worth it.

You fight and thrash violently, but your bonds hold strong. The chair rocks, and you lose your balance.

Crash!

You hit the cold, damp stone. It's sticky. A dull noise spills into your vision.

You swear, the sound echoes subtly.

"Why so vulguar?" a scratchy voice mocks.

The creature laughs at you.

"What a pathetic, lothesome creature. I like your attitude. You thrashed so hard I thought you might actually put up a fight."

Footsteps crash in rhythm. Closer. Closer.

It's standing above you, a dominating presence. It snaps it's fingers. A candle flickers on in front of you. The beast stands over you, breathing heavy.

"Oh, you sweet, beautiful fool."

The creatures face is but inches from yours, now. Its horrible grin stretches inhumanly. It's eyes, hollow and sunken.

"You will make a nice addition to my collection."

A sharp pain in your neck. You've been stabbed.

It continues hacking and chopping. You perish quickly.

Your face now floats in pieces in one of the beast's many jars.

Sometimes, you must take action when you most want to succumb.

Welcome back.
It seems your fate brought you back here.
Tell me, what do you fear?

"Ah! So you do have some fight left! That is more like it."

The creature pulls out a long, sharp knife.

It cuts you free, and helps you up.

You scramble to your feet, and tear off into the dark. Within moments, you smash into an opposing wall.

You trace the wall.

The creature cackles. It echoes around the room.

The stone wall becomes wood. A heavy door.

You pull on the handle, it's locked.

You slam and pound on the door with your entire body, screaming and begging for someone on the other side to open it.

Soon, your body aches, you grow tired. Nobody is coming. You slip down the face of the door, and land on the ground, exhausted.

The creature is still on the other side of the room, barely illuminated by candle light.

You've been splattered against the wooden door.

Doors that you thought were open to you may no longer be. Check, before they're locked.
"What a pathetic and horrible suggestion, to sacrifice an innocent for yourself? To waste such potential? To think I'd want a baby, instead of your supple flesh?".

"You will make a nice addition to my collection."

A sharp pain in your neck. You've been stabbed.

It continues hacking and chopping. You perish quickly.

Your face now floats in pieces in one of the beast's many jars.

Sometimes, you must take action when you most want to succumb.
"Your blood... yes. This I can accept. Come with me, I have something to show you."
"I have no interest in material objects. Such things mean nothing to me. It's you, that I want."

"You will make a nice addition to my collection."

A sharp pain in your neck. You've been stabbed.

It continues hacking and chopping. You perish quickly.

Your face now floats in pieces in one of the beast's many jars.

Sometimes, you must take action when you most want to succumb.

"What are you?" You ask.

The creature's hand remains locked tight around your arm.

"I am the Zagnar, The Gatekeeper."
The creature's hand remains locked tight around your arm.
"There is something I need you to do."
Within moments, the creature has drawn a knife, and decapitated you. You die instantly.

Your face now floats in pieces in one of the beast's many jars.

Sometimes, you must take action when you most want to succumb.

"My, my, so full of vigor you are."

Footsteps crash in rhythm. Closer. Closer.

It's standing above
you, a dominating presence. It snaps it's fingers. A candle flickers on
in front of you. The beast stands over you, breathing heavy.

The creatures face is but inches from yours, now. Its horrible grin stretches inhumanly. It's eyes, hollow and sunken.

The creature pulls out a long, sharp knife.

It cuts you free, and helps you up.

It hands you it's gnarled blade.

"I am Zagnar, the Gatekeeper. I will grant your wish, raise your blade."
You lie there, numb to your surroundings. Your vision starts to dance, as a fuzzy noise overcomes your sight.

Your breath slows. The dark breathes with you.

It starts to feel less scary, less lonely. It becomes like a blanket. The cold floor.

You lay for who knows how long. Time stretches and shrinks here, in the void.

You are calm, and peaceful, a sense of clarity overwhelms you.

Voices overwhelm you, revealing secrets of the universe.

Horrible, beautiful, a cacophony of emotions, empires rising and falling -- lies, betrayal, love, all at once!

Your third eye opens.

You become one with the dark. A primordial being. Some sort of fucked up god, cursed forever to bear witness to history and humanity, with no influence on it's outcome.

Cursed to know everything.

You fight tirelessly against your situation that moments ago you gave up on. Halfheartedly, you push back the darkness, not giving into it's incessant demands.

Voices whisper to you, begging you to let go, to be free, to let the darkness take you, but you continue to resist.

Days pass, but it feels like only moments. You're starving, for food and for stimulation.

You burn the last of your energy thrashing and flailing. It's all you had in you, and it wasn't enough. You were too weak.

The rats devour your corpse, now a skeleton tied to a chair, awaiting the next poor soul to find it.

Sometimes, fighting isn't the way out of the situation. Sometimes, you must take a step back and learn to embrace your environment.

The creature stops at a huge, locked door. With a booming voice it calls:

"I, Zagnar the Gatekeeper, demand this gate open!"

With the creaking of a century of neglect, the gate insists itself open.

Inside, a hunchbacked rat-man eagerly awaited his master. It squeaks and squawks.

"Grog, fetch me Humoncule." -- Grog moves swiftly into another room.

With a wave of his hand, Zagnar slams the giant door behind you.

It's like a sewer, a cathedral, and a laboratory had some kind of fucked up baby.

Heads in jars sandwich rusty surgical equipment.

What exactly is he doing in here?

Within arms reach is a rusty hacksaw.
"What's the biggest beast you've ever slain?"

You feebly attempt small talk with Zagnar.

"What is wrong with you, mortal fool?! Silence. It's golden."
"Ah, you are clever. Choosing a weapon of your own volition, as if you know what awaits you. I dare you not raise that against me, and save it for when it will be needed."

"It's time." Zagnar's horrible voice rattles through your bones.

He leads you through winding tunnels, steep staircases, and sporing mushrooms.

Eventually, you reach what looks like a wal-mart coliseum, with tens of adoring fans. They chant Ho-Mun-Cule! ho-mun-cule!

From a gated door, he appears. A horrible, mutated beast, disfigured and morphed. The crowd goes ape-shit. He slams his raggedy sword and shield together.

"If you win, I shall reward you. You can become my new champion."

Homuncule charges towards you.

He snickers.

"Well, you do know the right questions to ask. Just recently, I traveled to the far away lands of Zardonia, my homeland. It was in search of the Great Orb.

It's not been seen in a millennium. I found an ancient text describing it's last known location-- the den of the Parthunax. Being a great hunter such as I, I crafted a new weapon: The Kombobulator. Cut through him like butter."
"A powerful artifact. I've yet to crack it's firewall, but when I do-- the universe will be in my sight. My enemies won't stand a chance.
"A fine weapon. Infused with dark magic, and smithed by the legendary Büt on the snow peaked mountains of Zardonia. A fine weapon indeed."

"You are here to fight for entertainment. You showed me you had strength in the darkness. Now, you will fight for your life.

Answer me this, do you fear me?"
"This will be your weapon. Use it well."
"Rat bastard he is. He stole my father from me, and my Orb. My damn orb. Fuckin' bastard. What the hell do you want with him?
"Do you now... well... prove yourself in my challenge, and I will help you find him. You will fight for your life. For now, though..."
"This will be your weapon. Use it well."
"Isn't he just an Animatronic Fortune Telling Machine?"

He's an  all powerful creature of unspoken power. Well, allegedly.
His most dangerous feature... his tongue. Do not believe what he tells you, friend, he seeks to use you. Laugh at you. Until he is bored of you, and then...
"Isn't he just an Animatronic Fortune Telling Machine?"
"He cuts your head off with laser beams."
HA! That's what he wants you to think. Though to be fair... he's cursed to that box. Trapped in a poor contract.
"That's enough. How do I get out of here?"
You are going to pick up the item, or not. If you do, a secret option will be unlocked.
You are not in the club
[!if:items:Zarblade] You are in the club!
You can either choose the secret second option, or you can't.
Ask the Rat to cut you free.

The DIRTY RAT laughs at you. He strikes a match on the ground. It's like a torch to him.

He holds a small, rusty sword. In his other hand.

"LOOKING A LITTLE DOWN ON YOUR LUCK, HUH?"

"You fucker!"
The Rat shanks you in the eye.

"Whatta pushover. Fine."

The Rat frees you from your bonds.
You are shrouded in darkness. You spend the next week slowly starving to death. Your calls for help fall upon the dank concrete walls.
You hear a faint squeaking sound. The skittering of paws on stone.

The rat scurries to you. He holds a small, rusty sword.

"Then fuck you, fleabag!"

He stabs you in the foot.
Give up and wait for help
"How do I get out of here?"
"You're in the catacombs, kid. Deep underground. Real fucked up place around here. Gotta keep your wits about you."
With some awkward maneuvering, you're able to grab ahold of your weapon and use it to cut yourself free.
The Rat, your only guide, is dead. At least, now you have fire.

You can hardly see even an inch in front of your face. The milky black of your vision completely disorients you. You blindly and slowly wander the darkness.

You think you see a pair of eyes open in the darkness, but as soon as you turn to look, there's nothing.

You start to hear voices, whispers, calling your name. The Darkness becomes you.

The match dimly illuminates the cave like room. It spills shadows across the walls, but at least you're not completely enraptured in darkness.

You hear shuffling behind you.
"What can you tell me about him?"
"Does it bother you? Knowing a god is real, and watching you? Does it make you feel insignificant?"
"Ha! Have I heard of him?! Who hasn't? He's only the god of this realm.
"What can you tell me about your god?"
"I just want you to stop saying weird shit."
"How do I get out of here?"
"Just the cycle of life, my guy."
"How do I get out of here?"
"How do I get out of here?"
"Can't tell ya. Happened a millennia ago, long before my time. Must only feel like minutes for him. Poor bastard."
"Imma nobody. I know my place, but my peers respect me. I ain't a pushover, like you, but I'm still a rat."
"You really think that? You think I ain't gonna be a bottom feeder the rest of my life?"
"How do I get out of here?"
"It ain't a bummer to be a rat. Doesn't make me not a rat. Shit, I wouldn't change it. Don't know how not to be a rat."

"Ha! Sounds like too much paperwork.
Me... king of da Rats...
Ahem... there's uh, something I'd like you to have."
"How do I get out of here?"
"My ma made those. She thought I could be king, too."
"Man, I knew you was an asshole. What, you want to fight or something?"
"How do I get out of here?"

"Depends where you wanna go. You go that way, you'll meet a fucked up beast named Zagnar. He's like a mad scientist or some shit.

Otherwise, you can go down those stairs to head further into the catacombs. Might be able to find an exit somewhere, but I can't take you there. Got buisness."

"Wait, before you go, follow me."

The Rat leads you to a chest.

"There's a weapon in there. You should arm yourself, ya know, it's dangerous here. It's too big for me, or I'd've taken it myself.
